    "B. Doppler EffectThe Doppler effect occurs when the relative motion between a wave source and an observer exists.",
    "It manifests as a change in the source frequency as perceived by the observer.",
    "When a wave source moves toward an observer, there is an apparent increase in frequency, while the frequency decreases when the source moves away from the observer."
